<activity xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="act-8a-1-1">
  <statement>
    <p>
      Let <m>f(x)=e^x</m> and <m>Q(x) = c_0 + c_1 x + c_2 x^2</m>.  We seek numerical values for the constants <m>c_0</m>, <m>c_1</m>, and <m>c_2</m> so that <m>f(0)=Q(0)</m>, <m>f'(0)=Q'(0)</m>, and <m>f''(0)=Q''(0)</m>.
    </p>
    <p>
      <ol marker="a.">
        <p>
          Note that since <m>c_0</m>, <m>c_1</m>, and <m>c_2</m> are constants, if we take the derivative of the quadratic function $Q$ using the <xref ref="sum-rule">Sum</xref> and <xref ref="const-mult-rule">Constant Multiple</xref> rules, it follows that <m>Q’(x) = c_1 + 2 c_2 x</m>.  
        </p>

        <p>
          What is <m>Q’’(x)</m>?
        </p>
      </ol>
    </p>
